description:
&lt;p&gt;A brand new opportunity has arisen at Great North Childrens Hospital. GNCH is a large Childrens Hospital, within the Newcastle Hospitals acute Trust, delivering a diverse range of regional, national and international specialist services as well as serving the local population. The Deputy Directorate Manager will be a key member of the GNCH leadership team working across the full spectrum of GNCH services and deputising for the Directorate Manager in all aspects of the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;GNCH has a Leadership team comprising the Directorate Manager, five Matrons and Assistant Directorate Manager working closely with the Clinical Director and Assistant Clinical Director. The postholder will support the directorate manager in&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Delivery of directorate performance targets and budget management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The management of all non-medical staff within the Directorate including direct line management of a specific cohort.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The development and implementation of corporate strategies and decisions within the Trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition the postholder will support GNCH’s developments within local, regional and national networks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants must have excellent communication skills, proven leadership experience and knowledge of performance and budgets. More importantly they must be committed to supporting and developing a culture in which clinical teams can continue to deliver the highest quality of care to children and families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for all essential and desirable criteria required for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full time 37 hours 30 minutes/week&lt;/p&gt;
